subject:

THE WIND IN USE (read Ps. 18:1-15
===================================================================
verse:

He mounted the cherubim and flew; He soared on the wings of
the wind. (Ps. 18:10)

===================================================================
reflection:

The Bible tells of God using the wind to help the people of
Israel to flee from Egypt, by driving the sea back so the
Israelites could escape the Egyptians. The Holy Spirit—the
creating, life-giving Breath of God—“was hovering over the
waters” (Gen. 1:2) when the world was in the making. On
Pentecost, the Spirit came to the accom- paniment of the
sound of a strong wind, Paul and others let the wind drive
them as they sailed to many lands as witnesses of God’s
grace. God is at work as He grants us “The wings of the
wind” (the Holy Spirt) to spread His message.


===================================================================
prayer:

Holy Spirit, Breath of God, fill our sails and carry us
where Your grace is needed most. As You once parted seas and
rushed like a mighty wind, empower us to witness boldly and
faithfully, spreading the good news to every shore. Make us
attentive to Your leading and swift to obey. Amen. (AI)

===================================================================
